data.rules:
## Objective

Beat the game as fast as possible.  Use of _Hero Mode_ is **not** permitted.  You must complete all of the following objectives in no particular order:
- Collect all 286 precursor orbs
  - Duped orbs do **not** count
- Obtain all Dark Powers
- Complete all missions and side missions, all mission rules apply:
  - You **must** complete all of the missions defined by the game in the Level Select Menu (See - [Mission Chart](http://i.imgur.com/4RvK2zL.png))
  - A mission is deemed _completed_ once it's end trigger has been hit.  Hitting start triggers are **not a requirement**, for example - talking to a mission giver prior to doing said mission.
> The exception to a mission being completed on it's end trigger is if you choose to finish your run at the Metal Kor fight mission.  In this case, timing would end on the final hit of a successful fight - leading to the mission being completed and the credits roll.

All secrets are eligible for use.

## Timing
### Start
The moment you gain control over Jak after starting a new game.

### End
Timing ends the moment you have achieved *all* objectives defined above.

013xe3d1.label: HD Collection
013xe3d1.rules:
## Version Requirements

- HD Collection on PS3
- HD Collection on PSVita

### Note For VITA

There is a glitch on Vita where you can toggle secrets on (infinite ammo, invulnerability, and infinite dark jak) before having the required orbs or finishing the game.  

This glitch is not allowed to be used in runs as you should never be able to use these secrets prior to killing kor (or collecting the orbs).  In a run such as 100%, these secrets can be used prior to completing the game and getting the required number of orbs as expected on all other versions.

xqkkkz9q.label: Trifecta Any% Relay
xqkkkz9q.rules:
Beat all three original games' Any% categories in a row and in order (Jak and Daxter: The Precursor Legacy -> Jak II -> Jak 3). A different player must run each game!

Obey the respective start and end timing rules for each game.

Debug Mode isn't allowed.

gq7ee7n1.label: Hexafecta Any% Relay
gq7ee7n1.rules:
Beat all six games' Any% categories in a row and in order (Jak and Daxter: The Precursor Legacy -> Jak II -> Jak 3 -> Jak X -> Daxter -> Jak and Daxter: The Lost Frontier). A different player must run each game!

Obey the respective start and end timing rules for each game.

Debug Mode isn't allowed.

8140yeeq.label: Act 1 NG+ Trifecta
8140yeeq.rules:
Rules:

Beat all three main games' Act 1 categories in a row and in order (Jak and Daxter: The Precursor Legacy -> Jak II -> Jak 3). (For Jak 1/TPL get at least 20 cells and reach the end of Fire Canyon.)

Obey the respective start and end timing rules for each game.

You must complete all of the missions in Act 1 in the order defined by the game in Level Select. Disc tray manipulation is not allowed.

A mission is deemed "completed" once its end trigger has been hit. Start triggers do not count towards this definition.

Debug Mode isn't allowed.
Pausing between switching & setting up the game is allowed.

All three games must be played on the same console.

Timing

Start
http://www.speedrun.com/jak1/guide/j1t2s

End
After getting the final hit on the Precursor Robot in the Eco Mine, on the black screen after the cutscene where the third cart falls on the robot.

run.comment: First 5 lap skips in a row, ive gotten dozens of 4s but this is the first 5th.

data.name: Any% All Orbs
data.rules:
## Objective

Beat the game as fast as possible.  You must collect all 286 precursor orbs (duped orbs do **not** count).  Use of _Hero Mode_ is **not** permitted.

All secrets are eligible for use.  

## Timing
### Start
The moment you gain control over Jak after starting a new game.

### End
Timing ends on whatever occurs last
- When you either get the final orb
- Upon completion of the final mission in the game which leads to the end-game credits sequence.
> At the time of writing, this typically refers to the final hit on a successful Metal Kor fight

data.name: Any% Hoverless
data.rules:
## Objective

Beat the game as fast as possible **without** the use of the _Infinite Hover Glitch_.  Use of _Hero Mode_ is **not** permitted.

The _Infinite Hover Glitch_ is defined as performing two `L1` tricks in a single jetboard jump.

## Timing
### Start
The moment you gain control over Jak after starting a new game.

### End
Upon completion of the final mission in the game which leads to the end-game credits sequence.
> At the time of writing, this typically refers to the final hit on a successful Metal Kor fight
